Brian, Theresa, Mike,
We have some new D&I functionality up on Inclign that I thought I would dra=
w your intention to.
The attached primer summarises the functionality, but we are saying that "i=
nclusion" is behavioral and the behaviors that make up an inclusive workpla=
ce are often a subset of the values of the organisation.
We can therefore generate feedback around the values of an organisation and=
 provide individuals with feedback against that set of behaviors - whilst a=
t the same time giving D&I leaders a different "inclusion" view of the beha=
viors that they can use to drive D&I interventions.
We have the functionality up and running on your "innov1" demo/sandbox.
This approach has proved an effective sales angle for us - simply because D=
&I often reports direct to the CEO and has its own cost line - thus avoidin=
g some of the HR procurement channel challenges.
Would be good to discuss when you have time - we are starting to pick up cu=
stomers quickly here in the UK now and would like to take another look at a=
 US expansion.
We also undertook to let you know about our activities in the US - Sky have=
 been a customer of ours in the UK for a while and so we are now talking to=
 Comcast about a US roll out.
Best Regards
Chris


